per-crate so the kernel-resident component can comply with the Linux
eBPF verifier's GPL-compatibility requirement while the userspace
components stay permissive:

  * Apache License, Version 2.0 — userspace crates and the
    workspace as a whole (see LICENSE)
      - umai-loader   (userspace daemon)
      - umai-tui      (terminal dashboard)
      - umai-common   (shared #[repr(C)] types)

  * GNU General Public License, version 2 — kernel-resident crate
    (see umai-kernel/LICENSE)
