The GPL-2.0 boundary is contained: umai-kernel does not import any
code from the userspace crates, and the userspace crates link to the
kernel program only via Linux's BPF map file descriptors (an ABI-level
interface), not source-level dependencies. Per common open-source
practice (Cilium, Katran, bcc), this two-license layout does not
"GPL-infect" the userspace crates.

